parameters:
Alright! We finally made it! This is the Lal-La
Village.

Actually, I'm quite close with the village chief
here, and he asked me to run the tool shop in the
village.

Doing business in the capital city is fun in its
own way, but I think there's a different sense of
fulfillment in running a shop that's needed in a
village like this.

\CLPapa has been kind to me, but ever since Mama
passed away from the epidemic, he's become even
more focused on business.

\CLAnd yet, I know that he came to this village
because the money was decreasing, and the truth
is, it was to escape from that place.
\CLI hope we can have a peaceful life here...
\CLI've been alone a lot in this village too.

\CLI spent my time reading books, keeping my distance
from both adults and children of the same age.

I'm getting distracted reading my book, so could
you go somewhere else?
He talked to me without hesitation
構わず私に話しかけてきた

\CLAt first, I was cold to him when he approached me
without hesitation, but gradually we became close.
\CLNow, he is also one of my important friends.
何も言わずに行ってしまった
\CLWhen I treated him coldly, he went somewhere.

\CLAnd so, when I'm alone again, I thought that it's
the right thing to spend peaceful time.

\CLSurely, at that time, I could only see the world
in shades of gray and could only think of
protecting myself.

\CLSorry, I heard you, but I couldn't help it... um,
this...

\CLYeah, from the moment I first saw you, I thought
you resembled this flower. I just really wanted to
convey that resemblance.
\CLThe flower handed to me was small and white.

\CLEven though it's the same color as my hair, for
some reason that flower looks so radiant and it
makes me feel uneasy.
Why did you think this flower resembles me?
\CLHuh!? You're asking that! Um... well... um...

\CLSee? You're small and... a-and!... really
beautiful... That's why, you're like it...

\CLIt was the first time I had been told such a
thing, and I hated the people around me... but I
hated my weak self even more for thinking that
way.

\CLJust because there's someone who says I'm
beautiful, why...

No matter how you look at it, I'm a sorry excuse
for a lady, but it seems like you have poor
eyesight.

\CLAn adult lady? No, that's not it. I'm not like
that at all...

\CLEven now, the person from that time still doesn't
see me as a grown-up lady.

\CLSomeday, I want to get back at them... Until then,
please, always...

I'm entering from the next door to the tool shop.
I didn't come here to play today.
I came to buy some items, you know!
Enter through the door right next to us.
